<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,787,886]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,823,849]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Biology.</emphasis>
Reared from galls on 
<taxonomicName box="[545,655,823,850]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glauca">
<emphasis box="[545,655,823,850]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Q. glauca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[730,917,823,849]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Cyclobalanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[730,917,823,849]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Cyclobalanopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and other undetermined oaks (
<bibRefCitation author="Lobato-Vila, I. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J." pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref46786" refString="Lobato-Vila, I., Wang, Y., Melika, G., Guo, R., Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. (2021 b) A taxonomic review of the gall wasp genus Saphonecrus Dalla-Torre &amp; Kieffer and other oak cynipid inquilines (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) from mainland China, with updated keys to Eastern Palaearctic and Oriental species. Zoological Studies, 60 (10), 1 - 28. https: // doi. org / 10.6620 / ZS. 2021.60 - 10" type="journal article" year="2021">
Lobato-Vila 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. 2021b
</bibRefCitation>
). Both the host gall and the gall inducer have yet to be confirmed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
